### 2. Temperature Data (Athena — curated + raw DB)
ETL is handled by `temperature_data_export_package` (read-only).
Use `load_temperature_data()` from that package to get clean DataFrames.

#### Sensor samples (hive temperature) — after ETL
| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `sensor_mac_address` | string | Hive sensor |
| `timestamp` | datetime | 30-minute bin (resampled mean) |
| `pcb_temperature_one` | float | Hive internal temperature (°C). Already cleaned. |
| `gateway_mac_address` | string | Gateway the sensor reported through |
| `group_id` | string | Hive group (merged from hive_updates) |
| `hive_size_bucket` | string | `'small'` / `'medium'` / `'large'` based on bee_frames count |

#### Gateway samples (ambient temperature) — after ETL
| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `gateway_mac_address` | string | Gateway device |
| `timestamp` | datetime | Measurement timestamp |
| `pcb_temperature_two` | float | Ambient (outdoor) temperature (°C). Null rows already dropped. |

#### Hive updates — after ETL
| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `sensor_mac_address` | string | Hive sensor |
| `created` | datetime | When the update was recorded |
| `group_id` | string | Hive group |
| `bee_frames` | int | Human-recorded bee frame count at update time |
| `model` | string | Model version associated with this update |

